                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                    },
                    "page": 194
                }
            ],
            "subtype": "sidebar",
            "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
            "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
            "image": {
                "type": "image",
                "name": "Additional Lore",
                "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
            },
            "html": "The combination of two symbolic and recognizable predators of the land and air (the lion and the eagle) is the result of devout prayer among ancient cultures to an equally ancient deity\u2014a now long-dead god named Curchanus, who once held domain over the beasts of the world. These first griffons were believed to be much more intelligent and guardians of the faith, but when Curchanus was slain by Lamashtu, the surviving griffons regressed to little more than beasts."
        }
    ],
